    "description": "A hot-path performance budget carries a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when its measured p50/p95 is within the published budget, the proof packet is current within its freshness SLO, any waiver is unexpired, corpus metadata and a benchmark-lab trace are present, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A budget that loses any of those carries a label below the cutline and never inherits an adjacent backed budget."
  },
  "release_blocking_surface_refs": [
    "surface:startup_time",
    "surface:restore_session_time",
    "surface:quick_open_latency",
    "surface:typing_latency",
